  "content": {
    "prompt": "Construct a program that obtains minutes and remaining seconds from the input amount of time in seconds. For example, 500 seconds contains 8 minutes and 20 seconds.",
    "source_code": "import java.util.Scanner;\npublic class DisplayTime1 {\n\tpublic static void main(String[] args) {\n\t\t//Step 1: Read the seconds\n\t\tScanner scan = new Scanner(System.in);\n\t\tSystem.out.println(\"Enter an integer for seconds: \");\n\t\tint seconds = scan.nextInt();\n\t\tscan.close();\n\t\t//Step 2: Obtain minutes and remaining seconds from the input seconds\n\t\tint minutes = seconds / 60; \n\t\tint remainingSeconds = seconds % 60;\n\t\t//Step 3: Display the result\n\t\tSystem.out.println(seconds + \" seconds is \" + minutes +    \" minutes and \" + remainingSeconds + \" seconds.\");  \n\t}\n}"
  },
